node.text:
Who's behind that mask: as we adjust to life in the age of COVID-19, the face mask has become an essential feature of our attire and routine, a means of protecting oneself and others from the spread of the virus. But throughout the pandemic, many communities have struggled to access adequate protective equipment in the face of global shortages. As the need for masks continues to escalate, many are wondering: how can we provide for a global society in which wearing masks has suddenly become as requisite as wearing clothes?
??
The solution, in part, is being offered by creative, community-minded individuals around the world who are stepping up to make masks for those in need. These people, many of them volunteers, are supporting relatives, friends, neighbours, frontline workers, and under-resourced groups by transforming the practices of cutting, sewing, and stitching into essential, even life-saving endeavors. Full story link in bio. 
? Brielle Perry ? Gregory Bull

node.text:
How does a standup comedian become such a dark storyteller? 
I have to remind people that it’s not me that’s gotten dark.  It’s the world.  You are seeing death and pestilence descend upon us like a thief in the night.  I’m an artist so my work is a reflection of the world I see.  Sure I was a comedian for most of my adult life but that is just part of my human experience. At this moment in time I find very little humor in the destruction of the American Dream.  You are now experiencing the nightmare that has drugged us up in an attempt to silence reality.  So when people say Kirk why is your stuff so dark? If you don’t know the answer then you are still sleepwalking through your life? LOOK AROUND. ?

node.text:
How does a standup comedian become such a dark storyteller? 
I have to remind people that it’s not me that’s gotten dark.  It’s the world.  You are seeing death and pestilence descend upon us like a thief in the night.  I’m an artist so my work is a reflection of the world I see.  Sure I was a comedian for most of my adult life but that is just part of my human experience. At this moment in time I find very little humor in the destruction of the American Dream.  You are now experiencing the nightmare that has drugged us up in an attempt to silence reality.  So when people say Kirk why is your stuff so dark? If you don’t know the answer then you are still sleepwalking through your life? LOOK AROUND. ?

node.text: @v8nate take me back one day x
Miss NYC ... amazing place
Miss NYC ... amazing place
@v8nate take me back one day x

HOPE

It was 2 years ago that we were in NYC as a family. The first time any of us had been and it was an unforgettable experience.

We crammed so much in to our four days ?

But on this particular day we did a guided tour at the 9/11 Museum, walked the High Line, caught an infamous NY Yellow Cab to see the Friends Apartment Building, walked to the HOPE sculpture (in this pic) on W 53rd St, took a leisurely stroll through Central Park to see the bronzed statues, Lennon and Yoko Ono’s Dakota Building and Lennon’s Strawberry Fields mosaic tribute, and the beautiful fountains and lakes. We called in to the NY Public Library for a quick squizz then had a short rest in our hotel room before going to see Frozen On Broadway that night!!! Epic Show ??

The City that never sleeps! ?

I live in hope that one day soon we will be able to go back and visit, ideally spending a couple of weeks taking in the Big Apple ? and experiencing more of what this amazing city has to offer.

It doesn’t feel like that will be for at least 3-5 years with the way this Global Pandemic is going ... and this is so devastatingly sad.

No matter where you are in the world ... stay safe, stay well, stay connected to people and live in HOPE that we will get through this trying time.
